tial reading for students, educators and practitioners of child and family social work. It features: • clearly signposted ‘theory’ and ‘practice’ sections; • over 10 case studies including those drawn from the author’s experience; • end of chapter ‘Key points’ summaries; • further reading suggestions. With expanded coverage of race and intersectionality, contextual safeguarding and critical child protection, the book champions the development of resilient social workers working towards a more just and equal world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFamily social workzGreat Britain. 0aSocial servicezGreat Britain. 0aSocial work with childrenzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aJordan, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311129965540uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/978144736931840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447369318423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447369318/original  a978-3-11-129965-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles